  "poem": {
    "content": "A crumbling column, brick by weary brick,\nAn ethics lesson the wind chooses to speak.\nI saw a mule, abandoned in the street,\nIts metal shoe lost, a rhythmic, limping beat.\n\nA camera shutter, eager to possess,\nThe crack that runs through her painted blouse.\nI want to move, to shoot a truer scene,\nTo unveil the heart hidden deep within.\n\nBut shadows darken, shifting in the light,\nA single unit, caught in endless night.\nThe city sleeps, a canvas cold and vast,\nWhere broken promises forever seem to last.\n\nTaking everything into its cold heart and grasp,\nI speak to the night, begging for a new future to grasp.\nBut here, beneath the moon's pale, watchful eye,\nI must abandon hope, and softly sigh.",
